and kind of lecture the
president of the United States.

00:55:20.441 --> 00:55:22.663
Thank you
for your hospitality.

00:55:22.763 --> 00:55:24.185
[applause]

00:55:24.285 --> 00:55:25.947
[Rhodes] Our view was.
they're clearly

00:55:26.047 --> 00:55:28.089
waiting for whoever's next.

00:55:29.971 --> 00:55:33.515
[crowd chanting "U.S.A.!"]

00:55:33.615 --> 00:55:37.159
[man] It is my high honor
to introduce to you

00:55:37.259 --> 00:55:39.722
the president of the United
States of America.

00:55:39.822 --> 00:55:42.445
Donald Trump.

00:55:42.545 --> 00:55:43.847
[crowd cheering]

00:55:43.947 --> 00:55:45.368
[message chirps]

00:55:45.468 --> 00:55:48.972
[Trump] I'm with you.
the American people.

00:55:49.072 --> 00:55:50.895
[Obaid] So Jamal put out
a series of tweets

00:55:50.995 --> 00:55:53.698
being critical of Trump.

00:55:53.798 --> 00:55:55.620
and then we got a warning.

00:55:55.720 --> 00:55:57.662
There was an official
statement put out

00:55:57.762 --> 00:56:00.065
by the foreign ministry
where they basically said

00:56:00.165 --> 00:56:01.707
that Jamal and I
didn't represent

00:56:01.807 --> 00:56:03.228
the Saudi government. pft.

00:56:03.328 --> 00:56:04.790
which is. okay. fine.

00:56:04.890 --> 00:56:07.513
but that. I took as.
you know.

00:56:07.613 --> 00:56:08.794
things are different now.

00:56:08.894 --> 00:56:10.677
You know. there's
new guys in town.

00:56:10.777 --> 00:56:12.639
Uh. it's time to be quiet.

00:56:12.739 --> 00:56:15.462
♪ dark music ♪

00:56:15.982 --> 00:56:19.026
[Kandil] speaking Arabic

00:56:45.135 --> 00:56:46.436
[Obaid] Saud al-Qahtani
called him.

00:56:46.536 --> 00:56:48.639
Told him. "You can't write.
You can't speak.

00:56:48.739 --> 00:56:50.761
You can't tweet.
You can't do anything."

00:56:50.861 --> 00:56:52.443
And I said.
"Let's just stop this.

00:56:52.543 --> 00:56:54.245
There's no point
in continuing.

00:56:54.345 --> 00:56:57.569
Clearly. we've become
persona non grata."

00:56:57.669 --> 00:56:58.970
Jamal was very upset
about it.

00:56:59.070 --> 00:57:01.733
He had a big name.
He was like. "What do I do?"

00:57:01.833 --> 00:57:03.135
[woman] What will you do?

00:57:03.235 --> 00:57:06.098
Like. will you be able
to go back to Saudi Arabia?

00:57:06.198 --> 00:57:07.740
In principle. I can.

00:57:07.840 --> 00:57:12.705
uh. but when I. uh. see how
many of my colleagues ended.

00:57:12.805 --> 00:57:16.630
either. uh. jailed
or banned from travel. uh.

00:57:16.730 --> 00:57:19.353
I-I-I...

00:57:19.453 --> 00:57:20.995
uh. I think otherwise.

00:57:21.095 --> 00:57:24.178
♪ dramatic music ♪

00:57:24.939 --> 00:57:28.062
[Kandil] speaking Arabic

00:57:36.111 --> 00:57:37.973
[jet engine roaring]

00:57:38.073 --> 00:57:40.716
[Salem] Jamal messaged me
from a new U.S. number.

00:57:44.481 --> 00:57:47.083
He dropped off some bags
to hold at my apartment.

00:57:49.286 --> 00:57:51.028
It's hard for me
to talk about Jamal

00:57:51.128 --> 00:57:55.953
leaving Saudi Arabia because...

00:57:56.053 --> 00:57:59.677
it pained him

00:57:59.777 --> 00:58:01.520
literally until the end.

00:58:01.620 --> 00:58:02.761
[sniffles]

00:58:02.861 --> 00:58:04.603
♪♪♪♪♪

00:58:04.703 --> 00:58:07.366
Alaa was so upset with him.

00:58:07.466 --> 00:58:09.488
and she had choices to make

00:58:09.588 --> 00:58:11.971
because she had a travel ban

00:58:12.071 --> 00:58:14.134
placed on her.

00:58:14.234 --> 00:58:15.895
And it was impossible
to reconcile

00:58:15.995 --> 00:58:18.699
because there was
no way out of this.

00:58:18.799 --> 00:58:21.061
As long as she
was married to him.

00:58:21.161 --> 00:58:23.224
there was no other option.

00:58:23.324 --> 00:58:25.546
[jet engines whooshing]

00:58:25.646 --> 00:58:29.070
The thing that I hope
that Alaa knows

00:58:29.170 --> 00:58:32.154
is how much he loved her

00:58:32.254 --> 00:58:34.656
and regretted the end
of their marriage.

00:58:36.258 --> 00:58:39.762
[Wright] Jamal and I
were talking on the phone.

00:58:39.862 --> 00:58:41.524
and he was very lonely.

00:58:41.624 --> 00:58:45.368
You could see
that he was-he was...

00:58:45.468 --> 00:58:48.732
he had made a huge sacrifice
in his personal life.

00:58:48.832 --> 00:58:51.775
[Khashoggi] Unfortunately.
many think the people

00:58:51.875 --> 00:58:53.778
of the Arab world
are not ready yet

00:58:53.878 --> 00:58:57.582
for that luxury of choosing
their own leader.

00:58:57.682 --> 00:58:59.744
and that's what we are
lacking until today.

00:58:59.844 --> 00:59:01.266
[Wright] Can I just jump in.
one thing?

00:59:01.366 --> 00:59:04.229
We shouldn't pass too quickly
over some of these reforms

00:59:04.329 --> 00:59:07.273
being very important to
the future of that country...

00:59:07.373 --> 00:59:08.874
But it was surprising to me

00:59:08.974 --> 00:59:11.277
that we had
such different takes

00:59:11.377 --> 00:59:13.079
on Mohammed bin Salman.

00:59:13.179 --> 00:59:14.961
I saw him as a reformer.

00:59:15.061 --> 00:59:17.204
[Bartiromo] Let me introduce
the vision

00:59:17.304 --> 00:59:19.526
behind something
of a revolution.

00:59:19.626 --> 00:59:22.089
Please welcome to the stage.
ladies and gentlemen.

00:59:22.189 --> 00:59:23.971
His Royal Highness

00:59:24.071 --> 00:59:26.093
Prince Mohammed bin Salman.

00:59:26.193 --> 00:59:27.535
[applause]

00:59:27.635 --> 00:59:29.938
[Rhodes] I found it to be
utterly bizarre

00:59:30.038 --> 00:59:32.380
that at a time when this guy

00:59:32.480 --> 00:59:34.743
is clearly cracking down
on dissent.

00:59:34.843 --> 00:59:37.026
is. you know.
involved in this kind of

00:59:37.126 --> 00:59:40.109
rash war in Yemen
that is killing people

00:59:40.209 --> 00:59:41.951
and precipitating famine.

00:59:42.051 --> 00:59:44.594
that he's getting great press
in the United States.

00:59:44.694 --> 00:59:46.636
[man] Begin with Saudi Aramco.
a strong public debut

00:59:46.736 --> 00:59:50.080
after raising a record
25.6 billion in the IPO.

00:59:50.180 --> 00:59:51.922
[Rhodes] But of course.
the U.S. business community

00:59:52.022 --> 00:59:54.765
was drooling over. you know.
an Aramco public offering

00:59:54.865 --> 00:59:56.867
that could be worth
trillions of dollars.

00:59:58.750 --> 01:00:01.613
Mohammed bin Salman
was vetted in Washington.

01:00:01.713 --> 01:00:04.977
New York City.
Hollywood.

01:00:05.077 --> 01:00:06.819
Silicon Valley.

01:00:06.919 --> 01:00:09.982
Every major aspect

01:00:10.082 --> 01:00:12.505
of American power

01:00:12.605 --> 01:00:15.388
rolled out the red carpet
for this guy.

01:00:15.488 --> 01:00:18.672
Mohammed bin Salman
is a trillionaire.

01:00:18.772 --> 01:00:21.675
and that's
all these people saw.

01:00:21.775 --> 01:00:23.717
Jamal Khashoggi's voice
was important.

01:00:23.817 --> 01:00:25.519
because it was one of the only
dissenting voices.

01:00:25.619 --> 01:00:27.001
I still see him
as a reformer.

01:00:27.101 --> 01:00:30.165
but he is gathering
all power within his hand.

01:00:30.265 --> 01:00:32.447
and it would be much better
for him

01:00:32.547 --> 01:00:35.170
to allow a breathing space
for critic.

01:00:35.270 --> 01:00:38.093
for Saudi intellectuals.
Saudi writers.

01:00:38.193 --> 01:00:39.855
Saudi media to debate.

01:00:39.955 --> 01:00:41.577
Uh. we've become
very good friends

01:00:41.677 --> 01:00:44.300
over a fairly short
period of time.

01:00:44.400 --> 01:00:47.584
and we are bringing back
hundreds of billions of dollars

01:00:47.684 --> 01:00:48.985
into the United States...

01:00:49.085 --> 01:00:51.668
[Wright] Trump recognized
a kinship.

01:00:51.768 --> 01:00:52.990
They're rich
and entitled people.

01:00:53.090 --> 01:00:54.872
They found common ground.

01:00:54.972 --> 01:00:59.117
And the kingdom saw him
as a benefactor.

01:00:59.217 --> 01:01:01.079
a kind of stooge
they could use.

01:01:01.179 --> 01:01:02.921
...million dollars.
that's peanuts for you.

01:01:03.021 --> 01:01:04.523
[chuckles]

01:01:04.623 --> 01:01:05.724
Thank you. Mr. President.

01:01:05.824 --> 01:01:07.566
[Wright] And so
Mohammed bin Salman

01:01:07.666 --> 01:01:09.368
became Trump's man.

01:01:09.468 --> 01:01:11.670
Trump's man
in the Middle East.

01:01:13.593 --> 01:01:16.636
[jet engine whooshing]

01:01:22.683 --> 01:01:25.746
[brass horns blaring]

01:01:25.846 --> 01:01:28.069
♪♪♪♪♪

01:01:28.169 --> 01:01:30.592
[Rhodes] Trump's first
trip as president

01:01:30.692 --> 01:01:33.435
is to Saudi Arabia.
which is totally bizarre.

01:01:33.535 --> 01:01:34.916
I mean. uh.
every U.S. president

01:01:35.016 --> 01:01:37.079
goes to Canada or Mexico.

01:01:37.179 --> 01:01:39.361
To go to Saudi Arabia
on your first trip...

01:01:39.461 --> 01:01:41.884
[chuckles]
...this-this is insane.

01:01:41.984 --> 01:01:47.110
♪♪♪♪♪

01:01:47.590 --> 01:01:49.693
And when I saw
that famous picture

01:01:49.793 --> 01:01:52.616
of Trump and Sisi
and King Salman

01:01:52.716 --> 01:01:54.258
with. like. the orb.
I mean. it...

01:01:54.358 --> 01:01:55.419
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:01:55.519 --> 01:01:57.501
...that said it all.

01:01:57.601 --> 01:01:59.664
You know.
Egypt's General Sisi

01:01:59.764 --> 01:02:01.306
is a brutal dictator.

01:02:01.406 --> 01:02:03.308
and King Salman killed

01:02:03.408 --> 01:02:05.110
the promise
of the Arab Spring.

01:02:05.210 --> 01:02:07.312
So clearly.
Trump was for sale.

01:02:07.412 --> 01:02:09.875
I mean. the Saudi ambassadors
are going around here

01:02:09.975 --> 01:02:11.277
telling everybody
that they've got

01:02:11.377 --> 01:02:13.119
Jared and Ivanka
in their pocket.

01:02:13.219 --> 01:02:15.621
- [men] chanting in Arabic
- [drums beating]

01:02:17.143 --> 01:02:19.085
[Rhodes] Whatever MBS's
wish list was.

01:02:19.185 --> 01:02:21.388
Trump was saying yes to.

01:02:23.710 --> 01:02:26.133
So it was pretty clear
that there's

01:02:26.233 --> 01:02:27.975
going to come
a point of reckoning.

01:02:28.075 --> 01:02:30.899
♪ tense music ♪

01:02:30.999 --> 01:02:33.401
♪♪♪♪♪

01:02:34.282 --> 01:02:37.566
[Anas] speaking Arabic

01:02:48.138 --> 01:02:50.200
[woman] The massive purge
of princes

01:02:50.300 --> 01:02:52.683
and one of the world's
best-known billionaires

01:02:52.783 --> 01:02:55.005
all arrested by a man
who would be a king.

01:02:55.105 --> 01:02:57.208
a man emboldened
by President Trump.

01:02:57.308 --> 01:02:59.650
[Wright] On November 4. 2017.

01:02:59.750 --> 01:03:03.014
these raids took place
all over Saudi Arabia.

01:03:03.114 --> 01:03:06.037
[people yelling]

01:03:08.080 --> 01:03:10.262
Many of the most prominent
businessmen.

01:03:10.362 --> 01:03:13.626
intellectuals were rounded up.
hundreds of them.

01:03:13.726 --> 01:03:17.070
and put in the Ritz-Carlton
in Riyadh.

01:03:17.170 --> 01:03:20.474
♪♪♪♪♪

01:03:20.574 --> 01:03:22.556
And they were held for weeks.

01:03:22.656 --> 01:03:25.839
interrogated. tortured.

01:03:25.939 --> 01:03:27.401
Many of them
were hospitalized.

01:03:27.501 --> 01:03:29.684
One guy. his neck was broken.

01:03:29.784 --> 01:03:32.527
His body was covered
with electrical burns.

01:03:32.627 --> 01:03:34.209
He was a general.

01:03:34.309 --> 01:03:38.093
They were shaken down
by Mohammed bin Salman's man.

01:03:38.193 --> 01:03:40.175
Saud al-Qahtani.

01:03:40.275 --> 01:03:41.657
That was a coup.

01:03:41.757 --> 01:03:45.221
♪♪♪♪♪

01:03:45.321 --> 01:03:48.104
[Soufan] Saudi Arabia
had different factions

01:03:48.204 --> 01:03:49.346
inside the royal family.

01:03:49.446 --> 01:03:52.229
Each one of these factions
have connections

01:03:52.329 --> 01:03:55.072
to economic elite.
to business elite.

01:03:55.172 --> 01:03:57.595
You have
the religious establishment.

01:03:57.695 --> 01:03:59.357
But Mohammed bin Salman
decided

01:03:59.457 --> 01:04:00.999
that there's only one faction

01:04:01.099 --> 01:04:02.640
in the house of Saud.
and it's him.

01:04:02.740 --> 01:04:07.826
♪♪♪♪♪

01:04:11.951 --> 01:04:15.254
[Salem] The ripple effect
from Al-Waleed

01:04:15.354 --> 01:04:17.857
being arrested was tremendous.

01:04:17.957 --> 01:04:20.580
Stock prices moved.

01:04:20.680 --> 01:04:22.663
It was seismic.

01:04:22.763 --> 01:04:26.146
Prince Al-Waleed
is an important investor.

01:04:26.246 --> 01:04:29.790
the most well-known member
of the royal family

01:04:29.890 --> 01:04:31.953
outside the kingdom.

01:04:32.053 --> 01:04:34.936
very firmly within
the center of power.

01:04:35.937 --> 01:04:39.842
[Wright] Prince Al-Waleed
had been Jamal's patron.

01:04:39.942 --> 01:04:43.946
And suddenly. you see on TV
that he is powerless.

01:04:45.187 --> 01:04:46.689
This is my Diet Pepsi.

01:04:46.789 --> 01:04:48.731
[Wright] He is praising
his kidnapper

01:04:48.831 --> 01:04:50.053
and telling everybody

01:04:50.153 --> 01:04:51.495
that he's been treated
very well.

01:04:51.595 --> 01:04:52.936
And all these rumors
really upset me.

01:04:53.036 --> 01:04:54.298
- [woman] Okay.
- I mean. because now.

01:04:54.398 --> 01:04:55.299
they-they went so far.

01:04:55.399 --> 01:04:56.380
All lies.

01:04:56.480 --> 01:04:57.661
You know. I've been always. uh.

01:04:57.761 --> 01:04:59.904
all the time here.
at this hotel.

01:05:00.004 --> 01:05:02.046
and. um.
everything has been fine.

01:05:04.128 --> 01:05:06.511
[Wright] When I talked
to Jamal last.

01:05:06.611 --> 01:05:08.874
he said he got out
just in time.

01:05:08.974 --> 01:05:12.638
He would no doubt have been
in the Ritz-Carlton.

01:05:12.738 --> 01:05:16.082
maybe in far worse
circumstances.

01:05:16.182 --> 01:05:19.105
♪♪♪♪♪

01:05:21.508 --> 01:05:24.591
[Kandil] speaking Arabic

01:05:45.254 --> 01:05:48.518
♪♪♪♪♪

01:05:48.618 --> 01:05:51.281
[El-Atr] Jamal was very sad.

01:05:51.381 --> 01:05:53.443
He lost hope.

01:05:53.543 --> 01:05:55.045
I said. "No. take it easy.

01:05:55.145 --> 01:05:55.886
You're free now.

01:05:55.986 --> 01:05:57.488
You can express your opinion.

01:05:57.588 --> 01:05:58.889
You have a freedom.

01:05:58.989 --> 01:06:00.371
because not to say
your opinion

01:06:00.471 --> 01:06:02.533
about what's happening.
that will kill you."

01:06:02.633 --> 01:06:05.737
♪ somber music ♪

01:06:05.837 --> 01:06:08.941
I know Jamal for ten years.

01:06:09.041 --> 01:06:12.665
And we become
closer and closer.

01:06:12.765 --> 01:06:15.348
I have a habit
to wake him up every day

01:06:15.448 --> 01:06:17.590
seven o'clock in the morning
because he was lonely.

01:06:17.690 --> 01:06:18.831
He was isolated.

01:06:18.931 --> 01:06:22.035
♪♪♪♪♪

01:06:22.135 --> 01:06:24.558
This went for a while

01:06:24.658 --> 01:06:28.402
until the middle of 2017.

01:06:28.502 --> 01:06:29.844
he sent to me a message.

01:06:29.944 --> 01:06:31.446
He said. "Hanan.
come and stay with me.

01:06:31.546 --> 01:06:33.248
Come. and they won't see you."

01:06:33.348 --> 01:06:37.572
♪♪♪♪♪

01:06:37.672 --> 01:06:39.895
I was very happy.

01:06:39.995 --> 01:06:41.497
He's the man I wished.

01:06:41.597 --> 01:06:43.979
but I didn't have a courage
to express it before

01:06:44.079 --> 01:06:46.342
because he was married.

01:06:46.442 --> 01:06:48.544
First time I managed
to come and see him.

01:06:48.644 --> 01:06:52.108
it was to celebrate
his birthday in March.

01:06:52.208 --> 01:06:56.273
Well. it was his half-birthday
party in March.

01:06:56.373 --> 01:06:58.476
and he was dating

01:06:58.576 --> 01:07:00.478
a really wonderful woman.

01:07:00.578 --> 01:07:03.341
It was always fun
to have Jamal happy.

01:07:04.342 --> 01:07:06.524
[El-Atr]
When we got married.

01:07:06.624 --> 01:07:09.328
it was the most beautiful
day in my life.

01:07:09.428 --> 01:07:11.170
and I will never forget.

01:07:11.270 --> 01:07:13.452
♪♪♪♪♪

01:07:13.552 --> 01:07:15.454
I think I'm in a dream.

01:07:15.554 --> 01:07:18.137
♪♪♪♪♪

01:07:18.237 --> 01:07:22.622
But he was very loyal
to the Kingdom of Saudi.

01:07:22.722 --> 01:07:26.627
so he was feeling very bad
because he lost his hope.

01:07:26.727 --> 01:07:29.230
♪♪♪♪♪

01:07:29.330 --> 01:07:32.053
He decide he have
to express himself.

01:07:37.659 --> 01:07:40.162
[Soltan] Fall of 2017.

01:07:40.262 --> 01:07:42.745
Jamal was in
self-imposed exile.

01:07:43.786 --> 01:07:45.007
We met.

01:07:45.107 --> 01:07:46.689
and he gave me
the biggest bear hug.

01:07:46.789 --> 01:07:49.612
It was really. really warm.
and then he started crying.

01:07:49.712 --> 01:07:52.696
He said. "I left my country.

01:07:52.796 --> 01:07:56.380
I left my family behind
for freedom.

01:07:56.480 --> 01:07:58.462
just to be free.

01:07:58.562 --> 01:08:02.386
And no one knows what that
feels like more than you."

01:08:02.486 --> 01:08:03.948
♪ ♪

01:08:04.048 --> 01:08:05.710
I learned later

01:08:05.810 --> 01:08:07.512
that his first
Washington Post article

01:08:07.612 --> 01:08:10.095
was published that hour.

01:08:11.136 --> 01:08:13.198
[Faris as Khashoggi]
"Saudi Arabia wasn't always

01:08:13.298 --> 01:08:16.722
this repressive."
by Jamal Khashoggi.

01:08:16.822 --> 01:08:19.005
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:08:19.105 --> 01:08:21.488
We spend endless hours
on the phone

01:08:21.588 --> 01:08:25.132
trying to understand
the wave of arrests.

01:08:25.232 --> 01:08:29.176
Are we going to be the core
of the Saudi diaspora?

01:08:29.276 --> 01:08:32.980
Al-Hayat canceled my column.

01:08:33.080 --> 01:08:36.064
The government
banned me from Twitter.

01:08:36.164 --> 01:08:38.386
I spent six months silent.

01:08:38.486 --> 01:08:41.410
reflecting on
the stark choices before me.

01:08:43.051 --> 01:08:47.316
Years ago. when several
friends were arrested.

01:08:47.416 --> 01:08:49.419
I said nothing.

01:08:50.179 --> 01:08:53.163
I have made
a different choice now.

01:08:53.263 --> 01:08:55.045
I have left my home.

01:08:55.145 --> 01:08:58.929
my family. and my job.

01:08:59.029 --> 01:09:02.573
and I am raising my voice.

01:09:02.673 --> 01:09:07.839
♪♪♪♪♪

01:09:28.222 --> 01:09:30.284
[Obaid]
He wrote that first piece.

01:09:30.384 --> 01:09:32.967
Next day.
his ex-wife calls me.

01:09:33.067 --> 01:09:34.569
says. "Look what he just did."

01:09:34.669 --> 01:09:36.331
Which. I was like. "But. Jamal.
we just talked.

01:09:36.431 --> 01:09:38.533
What's going on?"

01:09:38.633 --> 01:09:41.316
Clearly. something
had gone very wrong.

01:09:42.998 --> 01:09:44.820
He had kept this very secret.

01:09:44.920 --> 01:09:46.942
That shocked a lot of us.

01:09:47.042 --> 01:09:49.025
and when it came
to Saudi Arabia.

01:09:49.125 --> 01:09:52.148
I always believed
that his loyalty was strong

01:09:52.248 --> 01:09:56.273
to his country
and to his king.

01:09:56.373 --> 01:09:58.956
I felt that
I had been betrayed.

01:09:59.056 --> 01:10:01.378
♪♪♪♪♪

01:10:05.423 --> 01:10:08.246
[Bishara] Jamal expressed
his opinion

01:10:08.346 --> 01:10:11.410
from Washington.
the seat of power.

01:10:11.510 --> 01:10:14.413
writing in the voice
of empire.

01:10:14.513 --> 01:10:16.015
The Washington Post.

01:10:16.115 --> 01:10:18.798
That could not be tolerated.

01:10:19.879 --> 01:10:22.021
[Obaid] He started writing
this. saying these things.

01:10:22.121 --> 01:10:23.984
and then
all these weird people

01:10:24.084 --> 01:10:25.545
started getting to know him.

01:10:25.645 --> 01:10:29.229
You know. uh. started to.
you know. hang around with him.

01:10:29.329 --> 01:10:31.192
tweet things about him.

01:10:31.292 --> 01:10:33.554
It became very bizarre.

01:10:33.654 --> 01:10:36.558
[dark music]

01:10:36.658 --> 01:10:39.281
♪♪♪♪♪

01:10:39.381 --> 01:10:42.244
[Maloney] Mr. Khashoggi
was publishing articles

01:10:42.344 --> 01:10:44.687
that were critical
of the Saudi regime.

01:10:44.787 --> 01:10:48.210
and so we called him
to request a meeting.

01:10:48.310 --> 01:10:51.134
Jamal Khashoggi
knew a lot of information

01:10:51.234 --> 01:10:54.297
about al-Qaeda
and Saudi support for al-Qaeda.

01:10:54.397 --> 01:10:57.060
So we wanted to talk to him.

01:10:57.160 --> 01:10:59.103
The meeting
with our investigator

01:10:59.203 --> 01:11:01.065
was the morning
of October 26th

01:11:01.165 --> 01:11:03.227
in the Virginia area.

01:11:03.327 --> 01:11:06.511
This was
a preliminary meeting.

01:11:06.611 --> 01:11:08.994
It became clear
that Mr. Khashoggi

01:11:09.094 --> 01:11:11.556
had a lot to say.

01:11:11.656 --> 01:11:14.199
[Wright] The morning
that he's going to meet

01:11:14.299 --> 01:11:17.403
with the investigator.
he gets a call from his son

01:11:17.503 --> 01:11:20.566
in Saudi Arabia saying
that their travel permits

01:11:20.666 --> 01:11:23.209
had been taken away.

01:11:23.309 --> 01:11:24.771
So essentially.
the Saudi authorities

01:11:24.871 --> 01:11:28.415
know that he's meeting
with this investigator.

01:11:28.515 --> 01:11:32.860
and his children
are being held hostage.

01:11:32.960 --> 01:11:34.782
[Maloney] The first thing
Mr. Khashoggi indicated

01:11:34.882 --> 01:11:37.145
was the recent news
about his son's

01:11:37.245 --> 01:11:40.208
inability to travel.
which upset him.

01:11:42.250 --> 01:11:44.113
I used to be
a federal prosecutor.

01:11:44.213 --> 01:11:47.436
and we had informants
that elected to testify

01:11:47.536 --> 01:11:50.600
against their coconspirators.

01:11:50.700 --> 01:11:53.163
If Jamal Khashoggi
had been an insider.

01:11:53.263 --> 01:11:54.965
and he was.
and had information

01:11:55.065 --> 01:11:56.606
that could be helpful to us

01:11:56.706 --> 01:11:59.610
and was willing to meet
with us and discuss it.

01:11:59.710 --> 01:12:02.693
that is a serious threat
to the Saudi government.

01:12:02.793 --> 01:12:06.097
The question is.
to what extent

01:12:06.197 --> 01:12:08.940
was the Saudi government
and the royal family

01:12:09.040 --> 01:12:10.942
entangled with al-Qaeda?

01:12:11.042 --> 01:12:12.424
Well. they were.

01:12:12.524 --> 01:12:15.147
Going back before al-Qaeda.

01:12:15.247 --> 01:12:17.189
they were funding
the mujahideen.

01:12:17.289 --> 01:12:19.472
and King Salman
was the principal bundler

01:12:19.572 --> 01:12:22.075
of all these contributions
to the mujahideen

01:12:22.175 --> 01:12:24.397
and then later to al-Qaeda.

01:12:24.497 --> 01:12:26.740
- [men chanting]
- [drums beating]

01:12:28.061 --> 01:12:29.603
Jamal would have known
about that.

01:12:29.703 --> 01:12:31.765
Jamal worked
with Prince Turki.

01:12:31.865 --> 01:12:35.009
who had been the head
of intelligence.

01:12:35.109 --> 01:12:36.931
and he facilitated
these meetings

01:12:37.031 --> 01:12:39.734
with bin Laden in Afghanistan.

01:12:39.834 --> 01:12:43.018
And who knows
what bin Laden told him?

01:12:43.118 --> 01:12:45.581
I mean. is there a person
in the whole world

01:12:45.681 --> 01:12:47.783
that knows more
about this relationship

01:12:47.883 --> 01:12:48.944
than Jamal Khashoggi?

01:12:49.044 --> 01:12:49.906
I don't think so.

01:12:50.006 --> 01:12:52.749
[chuckling]

01:12:52.849 --> 01:12:54.751
[Maloney] The Saudis claimed
that they enjoyed immunity

01:12:54.851 --> 01:12:57.114
even if all our allegations
were true.

01:12:57.214 --> 01:13:01.118
They hired lobbyists
in Washington.

01:13:01.218 --> 01:13:05.563
and Saud al-Qahtani's name
appears on some of the forms.

01:13:05.663 --> 01:13:07.685
His official title
had something to do

01:13:07.785 --> 01:13:09.688
with media
and public relations.

01:13:09.788 --> 01:13:11.009
but the easiest way
to describe him

01:13:11.109 --> 01:13:13.111
is-is MBS's henchman.

01:13:14.433 --> 01:13:16.415
Qahtani. on behalf
of the crown prince.

01:13:16.515 --> 01:13:18.497
hired the lobbyists

01:13:18.597 --> 01:13:21.120
specifically
to kill this lawsuit.

01:13:23.643 --> 01:13:26.306
Jamal Khashoggi agreed
to a follow-up meeting.

01:13:26.406 --> 01:13:29.409
He agreed to come to our
office here in New York.

01:13:30.931 --> 01:13:34.595
What he would say and what he
would be willing to disclose.

01:13:34.695 --> 01:13:37.038
we'll never know.

01:13:37.138 --> 01:13:40.221
♪ tense music ♪

01:13:45.027 --> 01:13:47.630
[brakes squealing]

01:13:51.153 --> 01:13:54.277
[messages chirping]

01:14:04.849 --> 01:14:08.713
[Salem] Saud al-Qahtani
unleashed hell on Jamal--

01:14:08.813 --> 01:14:11.716
the trolls. the bots.
whatever they are.

01:14:11.816 --> 01:14:16.321
the turning of friends
and former colleagues--

01:14:16.421 --> 01:14:17.883
all of that.

01:14:17.983 --> 01:14:19.966
He was threatened
and intimidated all the time.

01:14:20.066 --> 01:14:22.288
Of course it was orchestrated.

01:14:22.388 --> 01:14:24.510
And Jamal knew that.

01:14:27.113 --> 01:14:30.497
[Soltan]
It was November of 2017.

01:14:30.597 --> 01:14:32.299
We were on our way
to grab dinner.

01:14:32.399 --> 01:14:35.543
and he says. "Guess what.

01:14:35.643 --> 01:14:38.386
Saud al-Qahtani
sent me a DM on Twitter.

01:14:38.486 --> 01:14:40.909
Yeah. he wants to talk."

01:14:41.009 --> 01:14:44.793
And you can hear the fear
in his voice.

01:14:44.893 --> 01:14:48.557
He answers the call.
puts it on speaker.

01:14:48.657 --> 01:14:50.920
Saud al-Qahtani starts off.

01:14:51.020 --> 01:14:55.125
says. "I am calling on behalf
of His Royal Highness

01:14:55.225 --> 01:14:57.367
Mohammed bin Salman.

01:14:57.467 --> 01:15:00.330
He's watching.
He follows your work."

01:15:00.430 --> 01:15:02.693
So Jamal. he says.

01:15:02.793 --> 01:15:05.336
"Please send
my warmest regards

01:15:05.436 --> 01:15:07.138
to His Royal Highness

01:15:07.238 --> 01:15:09.060
and convey to him

01:15:09.160 --> 01:15:12.504
that when there are
positive reforms happening.

01:15:12.604 --> 01:15:16.148
we will most definitely
welcome them.

01:15:16.248 --> 01:15:20.453
When there are transgressions.
we will be critical."

01:15:21.854 --> 01:15:23.997
This was a moment
that I realized

01:15:24.097 --> 01:15:27.360
this is a noble man;
this is a courageous man.

01:15:27.460 --> 01:15:29.683
This man was very serious

01:15:29.783 --> 01:15:32.126
about the evolution
that he was making.

01:15:32.226 --> 01:15:34.388
[birds chirping]

01:15:38.793 --> 01:15:40.695
[El-Atr] If you hear
Jamal was faithful

01:15:40.795 --> 01:15:43.578
to the Kingdom of Saudi.
this is the truth.

01:15:43.678 --> 01:15:45.681
He used to defend them.

01:15:47.603 --> 01:15:51.307
But he think his duty
is to advise.

01:15:51.407 --> 01:15:52.708
to say his opinion

01:15:52.808 --> 01:15:54.931
before things lead
to a bad stage.

01:15:56.813 --> 01:15:59.476
[Soltan] Jamal had asked me
to be on the lookout.

01:15:59.576 --> 01:16:02.399
kind of play matchmaker.
[chuckles]

01:16:02.499 --> 01:16:04.321
And I tried; I tried
connecting him to someone.

01:16:04.421 --> 01:16:09.007
♪♪♪♪♪

01:16:09.107 --> 01:16:10.568
He was very. very lonely.

01:16:10.668 --> 01:16:13.251
He had just
gotten a divorce.

01:16:13.351 --> 01:16:16.575
I didn't know about Hanan.

01:16:16.675 --> 01:16:17.896
[El-Atr]
After we got married.

01:16:17.996 --> 01:16:21.701
Jamal want to spend
as much time together.

01:16:21.801 --> 01:16:23.863
He doesn't want anyone
to take him away from me.

01:16:23.963 --> 01:16:26.386
and that's why
we don't even like

01:16:26.486 --> 01:16:27.988
to go and spend long time out.

01:16:28.088 --> 01:16:31.071
We want to be just together
away from people.

01:16:31.171 --> 01:16:33.714
♪♪♪♪♪

01:16:33.814 --> 01:16:35.636
[Soltan] If you interview
anybody that tells you

01:16:35.736 --> 01:16:38.079
that they know every aspect
of Jamal's life.

01:16:38.179 --> 01:16:41.443
they are 100% lying to you.

01:16:41.543 --> 01:16:44.566
Jamal chose what information

01:16:44.666 --> 01:16:47.549
he shared with each person.

01:16:50.272 --> 01:16:52.455
This will be broadcasted
in a few days.

01:16:52.555 --> 01:16:54.737
not. uh. right away. right?

01:16:54.837 --> 01:16:56.019
[woman] It'll be. um--

01:16:56.119 --> 01:16:58.542
It'll go on air. uh.
Tuesday night. actually.

01:16:58.642 --> 01:17:01.945
the night that. um.
MBS is in Washington.

01:17:02.045 --> 01:17:03.707
- All right.
- It will be after...

01:17:03.807 --> 01:17:07.111
after MBS has met. uh. Trump.

01:17:07.211 --> 01:17:09.033
All right.

01:17:09.133 --> 01:17:11.476
[Soltan] He knew
what the stakes were.

01:17:11.576 --> 01:17:15.000
and knowing
all of those stakes

01:17:15.100 --> 01:17:19.925
and then still deciding
to go ahead

01:17:20.025 --> 01:17:22.288
and speak freely

01:17:22.388 --> 01:17:23.930
was very courageous of him.

01:17:24.030 --> 01:17:26.453
[woman] And why did you
self-exile?

01:17:26.553 --> 01:17:29.976
I just felt. uh.
whatever narrow space I had

01:17:30.076 --> 01:17:32.739
was getting narrower.
and I just thought

01:17:32.839 --> 01:17:35.142
it was better for me to leave.

01:17:35.242 --> 01:17:39.427
And. uh. actually.
right after I left. uh.

01:17:39.527 --> 01:17:41.109
arrests began to happen.

01:17:41.209 --> 01:17:45.113
Many of my acquaintances.
friends. colleagues

01:17:45.213 --> 01:17:48.477
were rounded up. and. uh-uh.

01:17:48.577 --> 01:17:50.840
I-I always regret
being away from home.

01:17:50.940 --> 01:17:54.844
but when. uh-uh. I see
what happened to them.

01:17:54.944 --> 01:17:58.768
I-I think I did
the right choice. uh.

01:17:58.868 --> 01:18:03.013
even though it is very hurtful
to be away from home.

01:18:03.113 --> 01:18:05.216
[Soltan] My way
of consoling him was.

01:18:05.316 --> 01:18:06.497
"Don't worry.

01:18:06.597 --> 01:18:07.979
There's a lot of people
like you.

01:18:08.079 --> 01:18:12.864
There's an entire community
of folks in exile.

01:18:12.964 --> 01:18:15.747
And so you'll find comfort
in that community."

01:18:15.847 --> 01:18:18.030
♪ uneasy music ♪

01:18:18.130 --> 01:18:20.192
But he didn't find
that community

01:18:20.292 --> 01:18:22.515
out here in Washington.

01:18:22.615 --> 01:18:27.660
♪♪♪♪♪

01:18:38.192 --> 01:18:41.035
[Karman] speaking Arabic

01:19:25.004 --> 01:19:28.828
[Faris as Khashoggi]
June 5. 2018.

01:19:28.928 --> 01:19:31.471
in this age of error.

01:19:31.571 --> 01:19:35.436
an Arab intellectual
rushes to praise the prisons.

01:19:35.536 --> 01:19:39.680
to write against the Spring.

01:19:39.780 --> 01:19:42.363
Another burns
the last of his history

01:19:42.463 --> 01:19:44.606
and his forbidden books.

01:19:44.706 --> 01:19:47.289
He says.
"We are not ready

01:19:47.389 --> 01:19:49.391
for democracy and freedom."

01:19:51.193 --> 01:19:55.418
It anguishes me to speak
with other Saudi friends

01:19:55.518 --> 01:19:59.482
in Istanbul
who are also in self-exile.

01:20:00.483 --> 01:20:04.067
I expect that I will
still wake up every morning

01:20:04.167 --> 01:20:06.510
and ponder the choice
I have made

01:20:06.610 --> 01:20:09.834
to speak my mind.

01:20:09.934 --> 01:20:12.917
We are being asked
to abandon any hope

01:20:13.017 --> 01:20:15.820
of political freedoms.

01:20:17.382 --> 01:20:21.667
This is a Faustian bargain
that I will not make.

01:20:23.349 --> 01:20:26.653
We are the kingdom of silence
no longer.

01:20:26.753 --> 01:20:31.137
[somber music]

01:20:31.237 --> 01:20:34.101
♪♪♪♪♪

01:20:34.201 --> 01:20:37.064
[El-Atr] Jamal in this time.
he was in Istanbul.

01:20:37.164 --> 01:20:40.188
Istanbul. it's very open city

01:20:40.288 --> 01:20:42.750
for different
Arabic background.

01:20:42.850 --> 01:20:44.793
and there is a lot
of activity there.

01:20:44.893 --> 01:20:47.736
He always go.
and he have friends there.

01:20:50.459 --> 01:20:53.963
[Soltan] I called him
when he was in Istanbul.

01:20:54.063 --> 01:20:56.285
and he said. "By the way.
I might be doing

01:20:56.385 --> 01:20:59.489
three weeks in Istanbul.
three weeks in D.C."

01:20:59.589 --> 01:21:02.252
So then I was like. "Oh. it
looks like you found someone."

01:21:02.352 --> 01:21:04.374
And then he was like.
"Yeah. I did.

01:21:04.474 --> 01:21:05.816
I really like her.

01:21:05.916 --> 01:21:07.418
We're gonna get married soon.

01:21:07.518 --> 01:21:09.500
I'll tell you all about it
when I get back."

01:21:09.600 --> 01:21:12.023
♪ somber music ♪

01:21:12.123 --> 01:21:15.086
[Salem] I didn't know
about Hatice.

01:21:17.369 --> 01:21:19.371
I knew about Hanan.

01:21:20.252 --> 01:21:23.355
But I-I didn't know
they had gotten married.

01:21:23.455 --> 01:21:25.398
So I'll say this.

01:21:25.498 --> 01:21:29.442
I think if you understand
the loneliness of that man

01:21:29.542 --> 01:21:32.325
in that last year...

01:21:32.425 --> 01:21:37.511
♪♪♪♪♪

01:21:38.152 --> 01:21:40.975
...I think things
that you can judge

01:21:41.075 --> 01:21:44.078
so easily from outside...

01:21:46.681 --> 01:21:49.144
...become a bit more nuanced.

01:21:49.244 --> 01:21:54.129
♪♪♪♪♪

01:21:57.653 --> 01:22:00.116
[El-Atr] Last call
between me and Jamal.

01:22:00.216 --> 01:22:03.080
he called to wish me
happy birthday.

01:22:03.180 --> 01:22:05.242
My birthday is 30 September.

01:22:05.342 --> 01:22:07.705
which is two days
before he disappear.

01:22:09.907 --> 01:22:12.770
[Salem] He messaged
from Istanbul.

01:22:12.870 --> 01:22:17.375
He said to me. "What if I just
go away to a desert island

01:22:17.475 --> 01:22:21.200
for a couple weeks.
couple years?"

01:22:22.361 --> 01:22:25.024
You know. he would-he would
come to me and say things like

01:22:25.124 --> 01:22:29.789
he was doubting his resolve.
and he knew how I would react.

01:22:29.889 --> 01:22:33.233
You know. a slap to the head.

01:22:33.333 --> 01:22:34.675
"Jamal."

01:22:34.775 --> 01:22:36.517
I remember saying these words.

01:22:36.617 --> 01:22:38.519
'cause they will
forever haunt me.

01:22:38.619 --> 01:22:42.363
I said. "You are in a war.

01:22:42.463 --> 01:22:44.966
and you can't give up.

01:22:45.066 --> 01:22:47.489
You can't disappear."

01:22:47.589 --> 01:22:50.412
Those are the last words

01:22:50.512 --> 01:22:51.894
I said to him.

01:22:51.994 --> 01:22:54.537
and I had no idea

01:22:54.637 --> 01:22:56.939
what I was even talking about.

01:22:57.039 --> 01:23:00.703
♪♪♪♪♪

01:23:00.803 --> 01:23:04.187
So on the 28th of September.

01:23:04.287 --> 01:23:08.112
uh. Jamal Khashoggi
and his fiancée. Hatice.

01:23:08.212 --> 01:23:10.675
go to the consulate to get

01:23:10.775 --> 01:23:15.039
an administrative piece
of paper for their marriage.

01:23:15.139 --> 01:23:17.202
They tell him to come back

01:23:17.302 --> 01:23:19.604
on the second of October
and that on that day.

01:23:19.704 --> 01:23:21.687
they'll have the document
that he needs.

01:23:21.787 --> 01:23:24.210
♪♪♪♪♪

01:23:24.310 --> 01:23:28.054
So the Turkish authorities
had somehow bugged

01:23:28.154 --> 01:23:30.256
the Saudi consulate.

01:23:30.356 --> 01:23:34.221
and almost immediately.
there are phone calls

01:23:34.321 --> 01:23:37.304
between the consulate
in Istanbul

01:23:37.404 --> 01:23:39.507
and. uh. Riyadh.

01:23:39.607 --> 01:23:42.390
And in the first call.

01:23:42.490 --> 01:23:44.472
it's a security attaché

01:23:44.572 --> 01:23:48.296
who speaks to an intelligence
officer. Mutreb.

01:23:50.138 --> 01:23:53.322
Mutreb explained
that Mr. Jamal Khashoggi

01:23:53.422 --> 01:23:56.766
is indeed someone
that is being "sought"

01:23:56.866 --> 01:23:58.087
and that they should proceed

01:23:58.187 --> 01:24:00.530
with some kind
of. uh-of mission.

01:24:00.630 --> 01:24:03.453
♪ suspenseful music ♪

01:24:03.553 --> 01:24:08.479
♪♪♪♪♪

01:24:11.602 --> 01:24:13.544
This special operation

01:24:13.644 --> 01:24:17.108
involved 15 people.

01:24:17.208 --> 01:24:19.871
Saud al-Qahtani
met the team

01:24:19.971 --> 01:24:23.275
before they left for Turkey

01:24:23.375 --> 01:24:26.759
on the Saudi government's
private plane.

01:24:26.859 --> 01:24:29.362
♪♪♪♪♪

01:24:29.462 --> 01:24:34.127
And Mutreb
was leading the team.

01:24:34.227 --> 01:24:37.531
and like every other member
of the kill team.

01:24:37.631 --> 01:24:41.175
he's a member
of the Saudi intelligence.

01:24:41.275 --> 01:24:43.017
Mutreb in particular

01:24:43.117 --> 01:24:45.099
had accompanied
the crown price

01:24:45.199 --> 01:24:47.983
on some of this missions.

01:24:48.083 --> 01:24:50.946
and he was someone
who worked closely

01:24:51.046 --> 01:24:53.389
with Saud al-Qahtani.

01:24:53.489 --> 01:24:58.374
♪♪♪♪♪

01:25:00.016 --> 01:25:02.439
[Obaid] Yes. it was Maher.

01:25:02.539 --> 01:25:06.323
Maher was a. uh...
was an intelligence officer

01:25:06.423 --> 01:25:07.805
that worked
at the Saudi embassy

01:25:07.905 --> 01:25:09.326
in. uh. London at that time.

01:25:09.426 --> 01:25:11.489
He was there
when we were there.

01:25:11.589 --> 01:25:13.811
and. uh. I introduced them
at one of our

01:25:13.911 --> 01:25:16.454
afternoon teas together.

01:25:16.554 --> 01:25:18.536
We were colleagues
more than anything.

01:25:18.636 --> 01:25:21.440
you know. and from time
to time. Maher would join us.

01:25:22.961 --> 01:25:24.103
To be fair.
he was a nice guy.

01:25:24.203 --> 01:25:29.288
♪♪♪♪♪

01:25:42.103 --> 01:25:46.347
[Callamard] Jamal Khashoggi
enters the consulate at 1:14.

01:25:47.228 --> 01:25:51.593
He is directed to the office
of the consul.

01:25:52.514 --> 01:25:57.399
♪♪♪♪♪

01:25:59.802 --> 01:26:04.427
He enters and finds
many people in that room.

01:26:04.527 --> 01:26:07.190
and so you can hear surprise

01:26:07.290 --> 01:26:09.473
because Mutreb

01:26:09.573 --> 01:26:12.156
and Jamal Khashoggi
knew each other.

01:26:12.256 --> 01:26:16.241
So when Jamal entered
the consul office

01:26:16.341 --> 01:26:20.325
and saw Mutreb.
he did express some surprise.

01:26:20.425 --> 01:26:25.291
but he welcomes Mutreb
in fairly warm terms.

01:26:25.391 --> 01:26:28.414
The conversation
turns very quickly.

01:26:28.514 --> 01:26:32.098
Mutreb is saying. "Don't
make it difficult for us."

01:26:32.198 --> 01:26:35.061
And you can hear the fear

01:26:35.161 --> 01:26:37.684
in the voice
of Jamal Khashoggi.

01:26:39.847 --> 01:26:42.690
[Kandil] speaking Arabic

01:27:00.830 --> 01:27:03.693
♪ tense music ♪

01:27:03.793 --> 01:27:07.197
♪♪♪♪♪

01:27:25.177 --> 01:27:30.223
♪♪♪♪♪

01:27:37.591 --> 01:27:39.893
[Callamard] The doctor himself
explained to Mutreb

01:27:39.993 --> 01:27:44.739
that it will be easy
to dismember the body.

01:27:44.839 --> 01:27:48.183
Joints will be separated.
It should not be a problem.

01:27:48.283 --> 01:27:51.086
[saw whirring.
plastic crinkling]

01:27:54.810 --> 01:27:57.673
[whirring slows. stops]

01:27:57.773 --> 01:27:59.155
At 3 p.m..

01:27:59.255 --> 01:28:01.317
CCTV captured people

01:28:01.417 --> 01:28:03.680
leaving the consulate
with plastic bags

01:28:03.780 --> 01:28:06.523
with the remain
of Mr. Khashoggi.

01:28:06.623 --> 01:28:09.366
The body parts
were carried out

01:28:09.466 --> 01:28:12.690
in several bags
and handed over

01:28:12.790 --> 01:28:15.853
to other individuals
who carried them

01:28:15.953 --> 01:28:17.175
into the car.

01:28:17.275 --> 01:28:21.299
And at 3:50.
those same camera

01:28:21.399 --> 01:28:23.542
record a member
of the kill team

01:28:23.642 --> 01:28:26.906
leaving the consulate
accompanied by someone else.

01:28:27.006 --> 01:28:30.790
This man puts on
Jamal Khashoggi's clothes.

01:28:30.890 --> 01:28:32.151
puts a fake beard.

01:28:32.251 --> 01:28:34.314
Could not put on the shoes.

01:28:34.414 --> 01:28:36.396
They didn't fit.

01:28:36.496 --> 01:28:40.601
And it was the shoes
that prompted

01:28:40.701 --> 01:28:43.164
the intelligence. uh. services

01:28:43.264 --> 01:28:45.086
when they reviewed
all the CCTV

01:28:45.186 --> 01:28:47.188
to say that's not Jamal.

01:28:50.271 --> 01:28:53.735
But this is meant to pretend

01:28:53.835 --> 01:28:57.459
that Khashoggi
left the consulate.

01:28:57.559 --> 01:28:59.261
and we do not know

01:28:59.361 --> 01:29:03.206
where Jamal remains are.

01:29:06.489 --> 01:29:10.173
speaking Arabic

01:29:22.747 --> 01:29:25.811
♪ suspenseful music ♪

01:29:25.911 --> 01:29:30.456
♪♪♪♪♪

01:29:30.556 --> 01:29:34.100
[all] chanting in Arabic

01:29:34.200 --> 01:29:37.284
♪♪♪♪♪

01:29:43.611 --> 01:29:46.213
[all] chanting in Arabic

01:30:02.912 --> 01:30:04.974
[Brennan] Knowing what I know
about Saudi Arabia.

01:30:05.074 --> 01:30:07.617
there is no way
that that horrific act

01:30:07.717 --> 01:30:10.861
was carried out
without the blessing

01:30:10.961 --> 01:30:14.145
and direction from the very top
of the Saudi government.

01:30:14.245 --> 01:30:15.666
There's just no way.

01:30:15.766 --> 01:30:17.188
[man] Senators
from both sides of the aisle

01:30:17.288 --> 01:30:20.071
are receiving the CIA briefing
they have been demanding.

01:30:20.171 --> 01:30:23.355
There's not a smoking gun.
There's a smoking saw.

01:30:23.455 --> 01:30:25.197
You have to be willfully blind

01:30:25.297 --> 01:30:26.919
not to come
to the conclusion

01:30:27.019 --> 01:30:29.522
that this was orchestrated
and organized

01:30:29.622 --> 01:30:33.927
by people in-under
the command of MBS.

01:30:34.027 --> 01:30:35.568
[woman] Mr. President.
why are you siding

01:30:35.668 --> 01:30:38.171
with the Saudis over your own
intelligence community?

01:30:38.271 --> 01:30:40.093
Because
it's America first to me.

01:30:40.193 --> 01:30:41.855
It's all about America first.

01:30:41.955 --> 01:30:44.538
We're not gonna give up
hundreds of billions of dollars

01:30:44.638 --> 01:30:47.101
in orders
and let Russia. China.

01:30:47.201 --> 01:30:48.543
and everybody else have them.

01:30:48.643 --> 01:30:50.345
It's all about. for me.
very simple.

01:30:50.445 --> 01:30:51.426
it's America first.

01:30:51.526 --> 01:30:55.450
♪♪♪♪♪

01:30:57.412 --> 01:30:59.355
[Rhodes]
Saudi Arabia can't exist

01:30:59.455 --> 01:31:00.836
without the United States.

01:31:00.936 --> 01:31:04.561
Their security guarantor
for decades

01:31:04.661 --> 01:31:06.783
has been the United States.

01:31:07.864 --> 01:31:10.007
The U.S. was in some way
responsible

01:31:10.107 --> 01:31:11.528
for this man's death.

01:31:11.628 --> 01:31:13.170
because the sense of impunity

01:31:13.270 --> 01:31:15.052
we give Mohammed bin Salman

01:31:15.152 --> 01:31:17.094
with this red carpet
treatment that he got

01:31:17.194 --> 01:31:18.456
and the embrace from Trump

01:31:18.556 --> 01:31:20.058
and nobody
really pushing back.

01:31:20.158 --> 01:31:22.220
I think he thought he could
get away with anything.

01:31:22.320 --> 01:31:23.902
and he was right.

01:31:24.002 --> 01:31:26.265
And it's just
disgusting to see him

01:31:26.365 --> 01:31:29.388
kind of grinning and
shaking hands with this guy

01:31:29.488 --> 01:31:31.911
who just chopped up
another human being.

01:31:32.011 --> 01:31:36.956
♪♪♪♪♪

01:31:37.056 --> 01:31:39.980
[camera shutters clicking]

01:31:53.915 --> 01:31:56.218
[Bass]
Good afternoon. everyone.

01:31:56.318 --> 01:31:57.619
This hearing
for the Subcommittee

01:31:57.719 --> 01:32:00.102
on Africa. Global Health.
Global Human Rights.

01:32:00.202 --> 01:32:03.226
and International Organizations
will come to order.

01:32:03.326 --> 01:32:04.467
I note that a quorum
is present.

01:32:04.567 --> 01:32:06.069
[gavel bangs]

01:32:06.169 --> 01:32:08.752
[Rundell] We have both
political and economic reasons

01:32:08.852 --> 01:32:11.395
to maintain a relationship
with Saudi Arabia.

01:32:11.495 --> 01:32:13.837
Saudi Arabia
is a strategic ally.

01:32:13.937 --> 01:32:17.121
and I do think that outweighs
the death of one person.

01:32:17.221 --> 01:32:18.803
Yes. it does.

01:32:18.903 --> 01:32:20.885
So there's
a paid political commercial

01:32:20.985 --> 01:32:23.808
for Mohammed bin Salman.
but. uh. you know.

01:32:23.908 --> 01:32:26.251
I-I believe that.
so any event. there you go.

01:32:26.351 --> 01:32:28.353
I thought that needed
to be said.

01:32:28.954 --> 01:32:30.956
[Bass] Ms. Cengiz.

01:32:33.679 --> 01:32:35.762
[Hatice sighs]

01:32:36.402 --> 01:32:39.566
speaking Arabic

01:33:05.795 --> 01:33:09.019
♪ somber music ♪

01:33:09.119 --> 01:33:11.942
[sobbing]

01:33:12.042 --> 01:33:14.765
Oh. Jamal.

01:33:15.806 --> 01:33:18.890
[indistinct chatter]

01:33:21.773 --> 01:33:24.456
[Kandil] speaking Arabic

01:33:39.352 --> 01:33:43.337
♪♪♪♪♪

01:33:43.437 --> 01:33:47.381
[Salem] The best justice
for him is a young person

01:33:47.481 --> 01:33:49.303
reading his writing.

01:33:49.403 --> 01:33:51.105
knowing about him...

01:33:51.205 --> 01:33:54.029
♪♪♪♪♪

01:33:54.129 --> 01:33:57.793
...being sure that those
that want him to be forgotten.

01:33:57.893 --> 01:33:59.995
that they will not win.

01:34:00.095 --> 01:34:04.981
♪♪♪♪♪

01:34:07.463 --> 01:34:11.508
Well. you know.
Jamal was a friend and. uh...

01:34:13.871 --> 01:34:15.933
...America and the kingdom

01:34:16.033 --> 01:34:19.136
have a toxic relationship.

01:34:19.236 --> 01:34:22.100
and it poisons not only
our own societies.

01:34:22.200 --> 01:34:24.823
but it's spread
all over the world.

01:34:24.923 --> 01:34:27.105
The chaos. the wars--

01:34:27.205 --> 01:34:29.748
America's had
a big hand in that.

01:34:29.848 --> 01:34:31.590
And Jamal's been
in the middle of that

01:34:31.690 --> 01:34:33.833
from his earliest days.

01:34:33.933 --> 01:34:37.657
He embodied. in some ways.
that relationship.

01:34:38.538 --> 01:34:40.280
But this contradiction

01:34:40.380 --> 01:34:44.805
became so nakedly obvious.
you had to choose.

01:34:44.905 --> 01:34:47.808
Which side are you on?

01:34:47.908 --> 01:34:51.172
♪ dramatic music ♪

01:34:51.272 --> 01:34:53.134
♪♪♪♪♪

01:34:53.234 --> 01:34:55.457
[Faris as Khashoggi]
The revolution is over.

01:34:55.557 --> 01:34:58.020
Its most important values--

01:34:58.120 --> 01:35:01.664
freedom. dignity.
and the right to life--

01:35:01.764 --> 01:35:04.787
have fallen by the wayside.

01:35:04.887 --> 01:35:07.831
The majority is unmoved
by the sight of the dead

01:35:07.931 --> 01:35:10.173
when they belong
to the other side.

01:35:12.736 --> 01:35:14.998
Divisions have even emerged

01:35:15.098 --> 01:35:19.043
between the detained.
the refugee. the cynic.

01:35:19.143 --> 01:35:22.667
and the dead that were never
celebrated as martyrs.

01:35:24.389 --> 01:35:27.252
I can imagine a young man
returning home.

01:35:27.352 --> 01:35:29.615
exhausted and bloodied.

01:35:29.715 --> 01:35:32.718
He weeps
for his dead brethren.

01:35:34.160 --> 01:35:37.744
Before going to bed
after Thursday's dawn prayers.

01:35:37.844 --> 01:35:40.787
the young man
murmurs to himself.

01:35:40.887 --> 01:35:44.031
"The revolution
is not over yet."

01:35:44.131 --> 01:35:47.314
The will of the people
is still the law.

01:35:47.414 --> 01:35:50.158
A new generation
must take the lead

01:35:50.258 --> 01:35:53.181
and look to the future.
not the past.

01:35:55.583 --> 01:35:58.847
One of the most beautiful
things I have ever heard

01:35:58.947 --> 01:36:02.291
is the call of the Prophet.

01:36:02.391 --> 01:36:07.016
In the beginning.
it is a call to freedom.

01:36:07.116 --> 01:36:11.301
That dream of freedom
is alive in us.

01:36:11.401 --> 01:36:13.303
ready to emerge again

01:36:13.403 --> 01:36:16.387
with the first sounds
of emancipation.

01:36:16.487 --> 01:36:19.550
[somber. stirring music]

01:36:19.650 --> 01:36:24.696
♪♪♪♪♪
